   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#  `representative_elementary_volume` "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Calculates the porosity of an image as a function subdomain size. This method works with extracting a specified number of subdomains of random size, then finding the porosity of those subdomains."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-04-25T01:55:08.799897Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2022-04-25T01:55:08.799533Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2022-04-25T01:55:11.076884Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2022-04-25T01:55:11.076287Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<Signature (im, npoints=1000)>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 1,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import porespy as ps\n",
    "import inspect\n",
    "inspect.signature(ps.metrics.representative_elementary_volume)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## `im`\n",
    "The input binary image of the porous material with void space voxels labeled with 1(True) and solid phase labeled with 0(False)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-04-25T01:55:11.081161Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2022-04-25T01:55:11.080902Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2022-04-25T01:55:11.283243Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2022-04-25T01:55:11.282702Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x432 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "np.random.seed(10)\n",
    "im = ps.generators.blobs(shape=[100,100, 100])\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize=[6, 6])\n",
    "ax.imshow(im[:,:,6], origin='lower', interpolation='none')\n",
    "ax.axis(False);"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The `representative_elementary_volume` returns a custom object containing the `volume` and `porosity` data. We can then plot the data to find the representative elementary volume (REV) of the porous material. REV can be found as the volume of a subdomain where any larger subdomain will have almost similar porosity values. In other words, in the following plot the point where the variation of porosity vs volume becomes a plateau."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-04-25T01:55:11.285700Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2022-04-25T01:55:11.285476Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2022-04-25T01:55:11.683451Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2022-04-25T01:55:11.682823Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "application/vnd.jupyter.widget-view+json": {
       "model_id": "58146615af6242d1816c544d73b14dd8",
       "version_major": 2,
       "version_minor": 0
      },
      "text/plain": [
       "  0%|          | 0/995 [00:00<?, ?it/s]"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x432 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "profile = ps.metrics.representative_elementary_volume(im=im)\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize=[6, 6])\n",
    "ax.plot(profile.volume, profile.porosity, 'r.')\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel(\"volume\")\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel(\"porosity\");"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## `npoints`"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "By default the method uses 1000 randomly located and sized boxes to sample as subdomains. Let's try a higher number to increase the number of samples:"
   ]
  },

   "execution_count": 4,
